author: wheetree
title: Disappointment compared to previous years.
review:
It's a heavy chunk of Damascus pattern looking metal, chained to a key ring.

Compared to previous year's Star Wars VIP rewards, this is very disappointing. 

It's heavy enough, I wouldn't want to use it for its intended purpose.  Definitely too heavy to use as a zipper pull.

This isn't even something with good display value.  You'd have to get close to know what it is.

author: StarKiller22515
title: The Beskar belongs in the hands of the Mandalorians
review: It is a heavy piece of metal that is not super big and has the imperial logo and wavy lines on it. As a keychain this would be terrible as it is quite heavy and would possibly scratch anything else you have in your pocket. Its neat for a shelf but you can tell what it is unless you have it in your hands.
